! SimpleEngine for CodeMirror 6

Replaces TiddlyWiki's native `<input>` and `<textarea>` elements with CodeMirror 6 editors, bringing syntax highlighting, autocompletion, and vim/emacs keybindings to all text inputs.

!! Features

* ''Syntax highlighting'' — TiddlyWiki wikitext highlighting in all inputs
* ''Autocompletion'' — tiddler titles, macros, and variables
* ''Keymap support'' — use vim or emacs bindings in inputs
* ''Bracket matching'' — highlight matching brackets
* ''Close brackets'' — auto-close quotes and brackets
* ''Spellcheck integration'' — browser spellcheck support
* ''Multi-cursor editing'' — same as main editor

!! How It Works

When installed, this plugin automatically replaces:

* `<$edit-text tag="input">` — single-line inputs (search, tag picker, title field)
* `<$edit-text tag="textarea">` — multi-line textareas

The original element behavior is preserved, including focus handling, placeholder text, and keyboard navigation.

!! Tab Key Behavior

By default, Tab/Shift-Tab navigate between fields (browser behavior). This can be changed to indent/outdent in settings.

|!Setting |!Behavior |
|Browser (default) |Tab moves focus to next field |
|Indent |Tab inserts indentation |

!! Keymap Configuration

SimpleEngine has its own keymap settings with a fallback chain:

